Feature: KYC completion dependency before virtual account creation is documented in the integration flow

  As an integrator using verification_link mode
  I want to know upfront that the user must complete KYC before I can create a virtual account
  So that I don't build a flow that silently fails at the virtual account step

  Background:
    Given I have a valid Bearer token from POST /auth
    And I set required auth headers

  Scenario: Creating a virtual account for a user in verification_link flow fails with status CREATED
    Given I created a user with "verification_mode": "verification_link"
    And the user has status "CREATED" because they have not completed the hosted KYC form
    When I POST to /v1/virtual-accounts with body:
      """json
      {
        "user_id": "<user_id_in_CREATED_status>",
        "type": "US_BANK",
        "bank": "austin_capital_trust"
      }
      """
    Then the response status should be 400
    And the response body contains:
      """json
      {
        "message": "User must be in VERIFIED status to create a virtual account. Current status: CREATED"
      }
      """

  Scenario: Documentation for verification_link flow includes prerequisite warning
    Given an integrator reads the verification_link documentation
    Then the documentation should explicitly state:
      "A virtual account cannot be created until the user has completed KYC and reached VERIFIED status"
    And the documentation should show the full flow:
      | Step | Action                                      | Expected status     |
      | 1    | POST /v1/users with verification_link       | CREATED             |
      | 2    | User completes hosted KYC form              | VERIFIED            |
      | 3    | POST /v1/virtual-accounts                   | 201 Created         |
    But currently the documentation shows steps 1 and 3 without mentioning step 2 as a prerequisite

  Scenario: Virtual account creation succeeds once user reaches VERIFIED status
    Given the user has completed KYC and has status "VERIFIED"
    When I POST to /v1/virtual-accounts with body:
      """json
      {
        "user_id": "<verified_user_id>",
        "type": "US_BANK",
        "bank": "austin_capital_trust"
      }
      """
    Then the response status should be 201
    And the response body contains "status": "activating"
